__pycache__/
*.pyc
.venv/

# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
# GENERATED PIPELINE OUTPUT
#
# Derived data. Rebuild it (`python run_pipeline.py`), do not commit it.
#
# Committing it is how the repo ended up with 102 stale knife-edge .dat files
# and 90 orphaned polar plots sitting indistinguishably beside the current ones
# - artifacts of runs made before the TE blunt existed. Anyone opening one of
# those .dat files in XFLR5 would have validated a section that was never
# screened and cannot be manufactured.
#
# The screen now purges plots/ and shortlist_dat/ on every run, so they are
# always rebuilt from scratch. Keeping them out of git keeps it that way.
# ---------------------------------------------------------------------------
screen_results*/plots/
screen_results*/shortlist_dat/
screen_results*/mesh_out/
screen_results*/*.png
screen_results_smoke/
mesh_out/

# What IS worth committing, and why (these are NOT ignored):
#   results.xlsx        the ranking itself
#   run_config.json     the exact config that produced it - reproducibility
#   kulfan_params.json  the exact ranked geometry; everything else derives from
#                       it, so the .dat files and plots are regenerable and the
#                       geometry is not lost by ignoring them
#   *.csv               robustness_summary, weight_sensitivity
